<h2>Anomaly FAQ</h2>
<p>In Ingress, anomalies are the most exciting kind of competitive event.</p>

<button>
  What is an anomaly?
</button>

<div class="card-body">
  XM Anomalies are large, competitive cross faction events run by Niantic. For a detailed explanation,
  please have a
  look at <a href="https://fevgames.net/ingress/ingress-guide/concepts/anomaly/">the Fev Games wiki</a>.
</div>

<button>
  Why is the anomaly in Brighton?
</button>

  <div class="card-body">
    Whilst Niantic made the decision to host the anomaly in Brighton for the Echo series, we're excited to host an event
    for Niantic in the vibrant and colourful seaside town of Brighton and can't wait to make it a successful and fun day
    for everyone!
  </div>


      <button>
        What type of gameplay does the Echo anomaly have?
      </button>


  <div>
      We don't know this yet, however we're hoping we will have more of an idea of the rules for the Echo anomaly series
      by the beginning of April.
    </div>



      <button>
        Why is there no Niantic registration?
      </button>
  

  <div>
      Niantic has changed how this works. It is now enough to just show up and interact with the
      designated
      event portals to get the anomaly badge, similar to the Second Sunday event.
    </div>
  

